{
  "texts": [
    "The integration of LLMs into hypertension research represents a forward leap, promising to bridge gaps in current knowledge and paving the way for more informed, data-driven decision-making in clinical practice.",
    "This study has limitations.",
    "First, the heterogeneity of study designs, methodologies, and NLP techniques across the reviewed literature complicates the process of drawing generalized conclusions.",
    "Differences in study populations, healthcare settings, and the specific objectives of NLP applications introduce variability that can obscure the aggregate impact of NLP in hypertension management.",
    "This diversity, while offering a broad perspective, limits the ability to apply findings universally across different clinical and geographical contexts."
  ]
}